# Database Rules — PostgreSQL

## Technology

Use **PostgreSQL only**. Do not use MySQL, MongoDB, or SQLite.

Default database name: `university_recommend`.

## Naming

- Tables and columns: **snake_case**
- TypeORM entity properties may be camelCase; map to snake_case columns with `@Column({ name: '...' })` when needed

## Current tables (implemented)

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `universities` | Schools (`short_name` e.g. HUST, location, tuition range) |
| `majors` | Major catalog (`field_group`, career orientation) |
| `university_majors` | Program at a school (training program, duration, tuition) |
| `cutoff_scores` | Scores by `university_major_id`, `year`, `subject_combination`, `admission_method` |
| `admission_methods` | Method codes (THPT, HOC_BA, DGNL, …) — imported from Excel |
| `users` | Accounts (`student` / `admin`) |
| `student_profiles` | Scores, interests, budget, goals |
| `recommendations` | Saved suggestion rows per user |
| `chat_history` | Q&A pairs with `session_id` (target: split into `chat_sessions` + `chat_messages`) |

## Relationships

```text
universities 1—* university_majors *—1 majors
university_majors 1—* cutoff_scores
users 1—1 student_profiles
users 1—* recommendations, chat_history
```

## Cutoff scores

- FK: `university_major_id` → `university_majors.id`
- `admission_method` and `subject_combination` are **varchar** today (not FK to lookup tables)
- Always filter by `year` when showing “latest” cutoffs

## Data pipeline

1. Edit or scrape into `mau_du_lieu_truong_dai_hoc_5_sheets.xlsx`
2. Run `npm run import:excel` in `backend/`

**Import behavior:** TRUNCATE and reload `universities`, `majors`, `university_majors`, `cutoff_scores`, `admission_methods`. **Does not delete** `users`, `student_profiles`, `recommendations`, `chat_history`.

## Adding data

| Need | Method |
|------|--------|
| Bulk update cutoffs / schools | Excel + `import:excel` |
| Single cutoff (link exists) | `POST /api/cutoff-scores` (admin JWT) |
| New university–major link | Excel/SQL today; API planned |
| User data | Auth + profile APIs |

## IDs

- PostgreSQL `universities.id` ≠ tuyensinh247 `school_id` from scrape API
- Map via `short_name` / Excel `university_short_name`

## Dev vs production

- `synchronize: true` in `app.module.ts` is for **development only**
- Prefer TypeORM migrations before production deploy

## Do not

- Invent columns not present in entities
- Mix ORM with a second DB technology
